HEADWORD: Jugal
<hw>Ju"gal</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L. <ets>jugalis</ets>,
fr. <ets>jugum</ets> yoke.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>Relating to a yoke, or to marriage.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Anat.)</fld> <def>Pertaining to, or in the region
of, the malar, or cheek bone.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Jugata</ent>⟦br⟧
